description:
French series.

A FACELESS ENEMY, A HUMAN HISTORY, A FIGHT FOR SURVIVAL.

The Oldis people once again bury one of their sons, victim of a devastating illness, the Feul, a scourge that ravages through the village killing without distinction of age, gender or race. Water seems to be the vector of the infection, but how can it be avoided? The discovery of a dead Bourouwn carried downstream by the river will reconcile two enemy tribes who must together discover the cause of the epidemic.
name: Le Feul

description:
This Flemish comic started came from the hand and mind of Willy Vandersteen. It's based on Johan de Rode Ridder (Johan the Red Knight) a character from the youth books by the same name that were written by Leopold Vermeiren. It's the publisher Standaard Uitgeverij longest running series after to Suske en Wiske.

History

The first 106 issue covers were originally blue with black and white stories, with the exception to number 106, which had a full color story. From issue 107 on the cover was in silver, with full color stories. They also re-released most of the blue series as full colored series with silver covers (added here as alternative covers). When Karel Biddeloo left in 2004 the cover got a complete makeover now with only the left side of the cover being silver.

De Rode Ridder stories were drawn and written by Willy Vandersteen. At first the stories started as normal medieval knight stories with a mythical element here and there. From issue number 19 (King Arthur) the Arthurian legend was woven into the story line. From issue number 44 (Three Mercenaries), Karel Biddeloo drew and wrote the stories on his own. He used a lot more Fantasy and Sword and Sorcery than his predecessor.
name: De Rode Ridder

description:
French series.

TWO TERRITORIES, TWO OPPOSING NATIONS...

... with only one thing in common: The Traks. Each country trains its champion to make him its herald, at the very moment when they’re preparing for war. As they progress, both champions experience personal upheavals, each one’s life being intimately linked to the evolution of his country. Their confrontation is inescapable…
name: Lans Sirling

description:
French series.

A NEW HISTORICAL AND FANTASTIC SERIES!

Rouen, May 30th 1431. Jehanne disappears in the stake’s flames. The legitimacy of Charles VII is safe. In 1436, Gilles de Retz has gone back to his land and this, to the children of Tiffauge’s greatest dissatisfaction. There is nothing left of the redemption he got from Jehanne. On the contrary, his terrible acts could threaten the throne.
name: Les Démons d'Armoises

description:
French series.

AN INSANE YOUTH SERIES BY THE ILLUSTRATOR OF THE BLONDES!

In the depths of space, on a far away planet... there are strange creatures. They are mean, dangerous and stupid. We don’t know them. They only think of stealing, killing, yelling, eating, etc... Only thing left to do is hope that they will stay home...
name: Les Zaliens

description:
French series.

SOMEWHERE BETWEEN “STAND BY ME” AND “HEROES”, “VIGILANTES” IS A HARROWING HOMAGE TO AMERICAN COMICS.

Four old friends just turned forty and live in different towns throughout the United States. They lost contact with each other, but the appearance of a politician seeking one of the highest positions in the country will bring them back together. They know him and are the only ones who know about the murders he committed over thirty years ago…

Back then, they had formed a secret super hero group called the “Vigilantes” to stop him. The time has now come to get back together…
name: Vigilantes
